radiographic_examinations.findings: Enlarged appendix measuring up to 15 mm in diameter with surrounding fat stranding and fluid in the right lower quadrant. Thickening of the terminal ileum, which is fluid-filled but nondilated. Numerous right lower quadrant lymph nodes not pathologically enlarged by size criteria. Bilateral hypodense renal lesions, statistically most likely cysts. Lung bases clear aside from minimal dependent atelectasis. No pleural or pericardial effusion.
